  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Any case diagnosed as congenital glaucoma with enlarged corneal diameter more than 11
             mm and intra-ocular pressure above 21 mmHg, including corneal edema or Habb's Stria
             with or without optic disc cupping.

          -  Any case diagnosed as primary or secondary congenital glaucoma to ocular or systemic
             abnormalities.

          -  Within the age of (0 - 12).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Cases of congenital glaucoma with previous intervention.

          -  Age above 12 Yrs.

          -  Cases with secondary glaucoma caused by surgical intervention, ocular co-morbidity,
             medications or trauma
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
